13/08/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX has appointed Italy's Silvio Bonfigli as the new head of its Justice Component, the mission announced on Thursday (August 12th). 
Bonfigli became a public prosecutor in 1992 and has years of experience as an anti-corruption expert. 
He replaces fellow Italian Alberto Perduca at the post. 
The Justice Component includes about 300 people, roughly 10% of the total EULEX staff, who work with their local colleagues. 
(Zeri, Koha Ditore, Express - 13/08/10)
